We used to play it twice through
First runthrough was an arc that cut through the free point line. You could choose to start on the right or left side, and shot until you missed. Once you completed HORSE from that distance, you moved out to the three-point arc.
So while it was perfectly possible to go 5/5 on the first set, most kids weren't good enough to shoot that many three-pointers in a row.
First to finish won, and usually the best shooter went last to make it fair.
